(19, 'Government Announces To Pay Salaries In Advance', 'The government has issued a notification to the federal employees to pay their July salaries and pensions in advance before Eid.', 'According to the notification, on the occasion of Eid-ul-Adha on July 31, government employees have been directed to pay their pensions and salaries on July 27.\r\n\r\nSalary and pension will be paid in advance due to Eid-ul-Adha expenses.\r\n\r\nEarlier, the Punjab government had issued a notification for payment of salaries and pensions till July 27.\r\n\r\nPunjab Finance Department has issued letters to all District Accounts Offices.\r\n\r\nIt is to noted that the federal cabinet has approved an increase in EOBI’s pensions on Wednesday (July 1).\r\n\r\nA meeting of the Federal Cabinet was held under the chairmanship of Prime Minister Imran Khan in which approval was given to increase the pension of Employees Old-Age Benefits Institution (EOBI).\r\n\r\nAccording to sources, EOBI pensioners will now get Rs 8,500 instead of Rs 6,500.', 'government-announces-to-pay-salaries-in-advance', 8, 1, 'post_main19.jpg', 'post_thumb19.jpg', 'post_list19.jpg', 4, 1, 0, 0, '2020-07-11 04:53:41', '2020-07-22 12:34:23'),
(20, 'Human Trafficking Ring Uncovered In Sukkur, Three Arrested', 'A Human trafficking ring has been uncovered in Sukkur, said police on Friday.\r\n\r\nAccording to details, police on the basis of intelligence, conducted operation in Jhangrdo area of Sukkur, where three men involved in human trafficking arrested.\r\n\r\nPolice identified the traffickers as Abdul Sattar, Peeral and Razzaq.', 'A Human trafficking ring has been uncovered in Sukkur, said police on Friday.\r\n\r\nAccording to details, police on the basis of intelligence, conducted operation in Jhangrdo area of Sukkur, where three men involved in human trafficking arrested.\r\n\r\nPolice identified the traffickers as Abdul Sattar, Peeral and Razzaq.\r\n\r\nThe accused used to buy women from different parts of Punjab and sell them in Sindh. Police raided in Jhangro area where women were being offered for sale.\r\n\r\nSenior Superintendent of Police (SSP) Sukkur Irfan Sammo said The recovered women will be handed over to their families. In Feb 2019, seven people were arrested on charges of human trafficking in Sakrand.\r\nThe suspects, which includes five men and two women, were arrested from Pir Zakari Colony. According to the police, the gang used to kidnap women and then smuggle them abroad.\r\n\r\nThe suspects fed the women pills to make them unconscious, said the police. A woman who was kidnapped from Lahore has been rescued too\r\n\r\nIn June 2019, The Federal Investigation Agency (FIA) arrested nine human traffickers including a woman during separate actions in various districts.\r\n\r\nIn operation headed by Deputy Director FIA Jamil Ahmad Khan Mayo and conducted in different districts the Authority arrested nine human traffickers including a woman and including Shafqat Bibi Shahid Sarfraz Ahmad Zeeshan Sajid Mazhar Iqbal Muhammad Shahbaz Muhammad Wazir Muhammad Rafique and Faizur Rehman.\r\n\r\nThe detainees were involved in looting the citizens in the name of sending them abroad for better employments there. Fake documents were recovered from their possession.', 'human-trafficking-ring-uncovered-in-sukkur-three-arrested', 8, 1, 'post_main20.jpg', 'post_thumb20.jpg', 'post_list20.jpg', 11, 0, 1, 0, '2020-07-11 05:05:56', '2021-07-28 02:52:46'),
(21, 'Song Featuring TikToker Jannat Mirza Is Out Now', 'Bilal Saeed’s One Two Records on Friday released a new song by Sarmad Qadeer.\r\n\r\nThe video of Punjabi song titled “Shayar” features TikTok star Jannat Mirza and Ali Josh.\r\n\r\nThe song marks Jannat Mirza’s entry into the mainstream entertainment industry.\r\n\r\nNearly 50k people viewed ‘Shayar’ on YouTube within an hour after it was released on the video-sharing website.', 'Bilal Saeed’s One Two Records on Friday released a new song by Sarmad Qadeer.\r\n\r\nThe video of Punjabi song titled “Shayar” features TikTok star Jannat Mirza and Ali Josh.\r\n\r\nThe song marks Jannat Mirza’s entry into the mainstream entertainment industry.\r\n\r\nNearly 50k people viewed ‘Shayar’ on YouTube within an hour after it was released on the video-sharing website.\r\n\r\nHowever, the song has mow gained 1 million views.\r\nEarlier, TikToker Areeka Haq had appeared in Asim Azhar’s news song “Tum Tum”.\r\n\r\nWith an hour of its release, the song had gained 130,000 views on YouTube.\r\n\r\nAsim Azhar promoted the new talent in his song, which also caused a lot of criticism when Azhar posted a picture with the TikTok star.\r\n\r\nApart from Areeka Haq, the video features Shamoon Ismail, Talha Anjum, Talha Younus, Hania Amir, Raamis, and many others.\r\n\r\nHaving millions of followers, Jannat Mirza has become the most popular TikToker in Pakistan.', 'song-featuring-tiktoker-jannat-mirza-is-out-now', 8, 1, 'post_main21.jpg', 'post_thumb21.jpg', 'post_list21.jpg', 0, 0, 1, 0, '2020-07-11 05:07:34', '2020-07-11 05:07:35'),
(22, 'Feroze Khan Celebrates 30th Birthday; Fans, Family Extend Wishes', 'Former Pakistani celebrity Feroze Khan celebrated his 30th birthday on Saturday.\r\n\r\nFans and friends extended love and wishes to Feroze on social media.\r\n\r\nFeroze Khan turned to Instagram to share his adorable photo and wrote: “Allah has been super merciful and kept it real and I pray for you all the same. The exact same happiness and cheer I swear. I love you guys. May Allah protect you all and your soul and and your dears, your repute and life and everything little and big.”\r\n\r\n“And never lose hope. Never! Fight and win and thank and fall and stand again and keep trying. Happy 30th to me Allhumdullilah he rabil alameen,” he further said.', 'Former Pakistani celebrity Feroze Khan celebrated his 30th birthday on Saturday.\r\n\r\nFans and friends extended love and wishes to Feroze on social media.\r\n\r\nFeroze Khan turned to Instagram to share his adorable photo and wrote: “Allah has been super merciful and kept it real and I pray for you all the same. The exact same happiness and cheer I swear. I love you guys. May Allah protect you all and your soul and and your dears, your repute and life and everything little and big.”\r\n\r\n“And never lose hope. Never! Fight and win and thank and fall and stand again and keep trying. Happy 30th to me Allhumdullilah he rabil alameen,” he further said.\r\n\r\n\r\nMoreover, Feroze’s sister Humaima Malick also posted a throwback photo of her brother and extended love and prayers to him.\r\n\r\nShe wrote, “Happy birthday, may Allah protect you hamesha hamesha Ameen! Live long be with me for ever and ever 🙂 #mashallah.”\r\n\r\nEarlier on the occasion of Father’s Day, many celebs took o social media to thank their dads for the important role they’ve played in their lives.\r\n\r\nFormer actor Feroze Khan also shared an adorable moment with his son wishing himself on Father’s Day.\r\n\r\nFeroze Khan Had Us Smiling\r\n\r\nHe had also announced on Twitter to quit the showbiz industry. Khan revealed that from hereon, he will only entertain monetary offers that promote the teachings of Islam.\r\n– my fans have been waiting for a statement from me. I announce that I quit the showbiz industry and will only act and provide my services for the teaching of Islam through this platform if needed else anything but this InshAllah,Request you all to pray for me and my loved ones.\r\n\r\n— Feroze Khan (@ferozekhaan) March 6, 2020', 'feroze-khan-celebrates-30th-birthday-fans-family-extend-wishes', 8, 1, 'post_main22.jpg', 'post_thumb22.jpg', 'post_list22.jpg', 1, 0, 1, 0, '2020-07-11 05:09:08', '2020-09-07 07:20:01'),
(23, 'Swiss Ambassador Eager To Visit Beautiful Areas Of Pakistan', 'Switzerland’s Ambassador-designate to Pakistan Benedict de Cerjat is excited to visit the beautiful areas of Pakistan for which he also tweeted a video of Pakistani areas.\r\n\r\n\r\nAccording to the details, the nominated ambassador of Switzerland Benedict de Cerjat tweeted a video of Pakistani areas based on the pictures.\r\nThis is just to share a first glimpse of my new home #Pakistan with my friends and followers in #Switzerland. Obviously, I have not seen all these places as yet – but eager to explore! https://t.co/O24BvcGQuR\r\n\r\n— Ambassador Bénédict de Cerjat (@SwissAmbPak) July 9, 2020', 'Switzerland’s Ambassador-designate to Pakistan Benedict de Cerjat is excited to visit the beautiful areas of Pakistan for which he also tweeted a video of Pakistani areas.\r\n\r\n\r\nAccording to the details, the nominated ambassador of Switzerland Benedict de Cerjat tweeted a video of Pakistani areas based on the pictures.\r\n\r\nThis is just to share a first glimpse of my new home #Pakistan with my friends and followers in #Switzerland. Obviously, I have not seen all these places as yet – but eager to explore! https://t.co/O24BvcGQuR\r\n\r\n— Ambassador Bénédict de Cerjat (@SwissAmbPak) July 9, 2020\r\n\r\nThe ambassador wrote on Twitter, “This is just to share a first glimpse of my new home #Pakistan with my friends and followers in #Switzerland. Obviously, I have not seen all these places as yet – but eager to explore!”\r\n\r\nThe Swiss ambassador says the video is just to show the first glimpse of his new home Pakistan with friends from Switzerland.\r\n\r\n“I haven’t seen all of these places yet, but I’m eager to explore,” he said.\r\n\r\nEarlier, the Swiss Ambassador had expressed his desire to explore different parts of Pakistan after his arrival in Pakistan.', 'swiss-ambassador-eager-to-visit-beautiful-areas-of-pakistan', 8, 1, 'post_main23.jpg', 'post_thumb23.jpg', 'post_list23.jpg', 0, 0, 1, 